---
// Homepage band — "How SpecScore compares." Teases the /vs/ hub with a
// compact mini-card per rival (name + one-line contrast), each linking to
// its full comparison. The full matrix lives on /vs/, not here.
---

<section class="compare section" aria-labelledby="compare-title">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 id="compare-title" class="compare__title">How SpecScore compares.</h2>
    <p class="compare__sub">
      Spec-driven development is a crowded space. Here's where SpecScore
      stands against the alternatives — honestly.
    </p>

    <div class="minis">
      <a href="/vs/plain-markdown/" class="mini">
        <span class="mini__name">Plain Markdown</span>
        <span class="mini__line">The default. SpecScore is what your Markdown graduates to.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/vs/openspec/" class="mini">
        <span class="mini__name">OpenSpec</span>
        <span class="mini__line">A solid on-ramp. SpecScore is the guardrails.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/vs/spec-kit/" class="mini">
        <span class="mini__name">Spec Kit</span>
        <span class="mini__line">Spec Kit is the workflow. SpecScore is the artifact.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/vs/datarim/" class="mini">
        <span class="mini__name">Datarim</span>
        <span class="mini__line">Datarim runs the pipeline. SpecScore is what it leaves behind.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/vs/codespeak/" class="mini">
        <span class="mini__name">CodeSpeak</span>
        <span class="mini__line">CodeSpeak bets on a compiler. SpecScore bets on a format.</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <p class="compare__more">
      <a href="/vs/" class="compare__more-link">See the full comparison &rarr;</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .compare { background: var(--cream-2); }
  .compare__title {
    font-size: var(--fs-h2);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .compare__sub {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  /* ── Mini comparison cards ── */
  .minis {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }
  .mini {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-1);
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--validator-green);
    padding: var(--space-3);
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 160ms ease, box-shadow 160ms ease;
  }
  .mini:hover {
    border-color: var(--graphite);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.06);
  }
  .mini:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--ink-blue);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .mini__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .mini__line {
    color: var(--mid-ink);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .compare__more {
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }
  .compare__more-link {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--validator-green);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .compare__more-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 980px) {
    .minis { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .minis { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
</style>
